ntration-mass relations in our simulations over the entire range of masses\nprobed (1e10 Msun < M < 1e15 Msun). Haloes in the WMAP3 cosmology (at a fixed\nmass) are more flatted compared to the WMAP1 cosmology, with a medium to long\naxis ration reduced by ~10 %. Finally, we show that the distribution of halo\nspin parameters is the same for all three cosmologies.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 14 May 2008 07:19:54 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 1 Oct 2008 13:56:52 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-13"}
